Jase is the original Bass DJ of Vietnam, he had been a pioneer of Jungle and Dubstep,Glitch Hop scene since 2007 in his native land. 

Jase self taught himself the art of djing in 2001, when he bought his 1200s.
 House was his first genre of choice for the first year. As Jase progressed, he found House's beat was to simple so the next genre was Nu Skool Breaks due to its popularity of it at that time in Sydney.
 He slowly moved toward Drum and Bass, Hiphop and Reggae after-co founded the infamous Sydney's DNB promotional crew "Foreigndub" which made numorous  successful parties bringing international DJs including DJ Marky and Stamina MC, Big Bud, DJ Patife & MC Cleveland Watkiss, Kenny Ken and many more. 

In 2007, Jase returns to his hometown Ho Chi Minh, and started The Beats, which focuses on promoting beat based music and brining international DJs to town, he also co-founded Saigon Rockers with party such as Reggae Sunday.

Dyro‚Äôs journey to the top has been fast and swift, marking him out as one of the biggest talents to emerge from an explosive new generation of artists. Solidifying his steps in history by becoming the youngest ever highest entry in the acclaimed DJ Mag Top 100 poll, remaining in the top 30 echelons of this prestigious list for three consecutive years.

Starting out on an upward trajectory ever since his inaugural releases, Dyro continuously crafted his sound via darker and more experimental strains of electronic music, including the launch of his solo imprint WOLV which saw Dyro further hone his original take on driving bass lines and grittier sounds.

Being stripped of regular creative outlets this past year has pushed Dyro‚Äôs creativity into new and unexpected areas. Next to bulking the STMPD RCRDS catalogue with steady dance floor stompers ‚ÄòMind The Grind‚Äô, ‚ÄòWarp Speed‚Äô, ‚ÄòHella Dope‚Äô and ‚ÄòBombai‚Äô, he‚Äôs added some massive remixes for Julian Calor's 'Moving Forward' and John K's 'Happiness' providing fans with a taste of what's to come. Jumping into 2021 with a Dyro x Conro collaboration titled 'Memory Bank', Dyro showcases he's not only ready to keep stacking thrills up in the 'Memory Bank' but more importantly - provide the soundtracks to them!

While by now it‚Äôs no longer surprising that Dyro headlines sold-out shows the world over and boasts an exceptional back catalogue overflowing with quality, it‚Äôs clear however the best is yet to come for this talented Dutchman.

Providing much-desired club content, Aidan Bega headlined one of Europe‚Äôs most inaugural sunrise dance spots in 2019- Cavo Paradiso Mykonos, aptly the exact establishment he fell in love with house music years before. He also played previously at the island‚Äôs late abode-Paradise Club. 2019 closed out at Festival X Sydney, alongside Camelphat, MK, Kolsch and Nic Fanciulli, welcoming a new season‚Äôs bank of infectious music from the studio to the stage.

Based in Bali, Indonesia Kaiser Waldon`s ever-expanding release schedule continues to grow as the Sydney native creates his sonic journey through effortless transitions with his energy-infused renditions of house, techno and disco.

Kaiser Waldon`s climatic rise on the electronic music scene has moved from strength to strength seeing the Bali based artist make his way onto the world stage with timeless form as his booking and musical release schedule grew exponentially over the last few years.

"Hard work and sheer grit brought me to where I am today, I couldn't be more grateful for how my journey continues to unfold"

An unrivalled love for the deep & funk his key music styles include a combination of House, Techno and Disco infused elements showing Kaiser`s monumental amount of versatility as he weaves his way through his musical transitions creating a total blur between what can be a key, genre defining element among his song selections and musical journey. 2018 and 2019 had some major milestones for the Sydney native as he found himself Playing for Resistance Singapore and Japan in 2018 and again Resistance Singapore in 2019, as well as BPM Festival Bali.

Racking up a hefty discography Kaiser`s collection of stellar EP releases has seen the DJ release on labels such as Double Up Records, Be Rich Records, Aathee Records and MYR Records in Germany with regular support from industry heavyweights like Joris Voorn, CLAPTONE, DOORLY, Roger Sanchez, Kollektiv Turmstrasse & More‚Ä¶

Currently based in Bali with residencies at the most sought after venues on the island including Mrs Sippy, Single Fin, Omnia, Vault Backroom, Old Man`s and Cafe Del Mar. Kaiser is also the Co-Founder of escape presents, an Event brand that holds its parties at Vault, Oldmans & Omnia.

Kaiser is a key figure in the Bali House community with his contributions to the scene as well as his personal desire to keep raising the benchmark of quality electronic music.

Dynamic percussion, full-bodied basslines and melodies that ooze with groove are the trademarks of Josh Glenny and Sean McDermott, who formed SEVADER in 2016. The project has won over audiences on several continents with their deep & minimal Summer jams which are paying dividends, on and off the dancefloor. 

The pair have travelled extensively to write so it‚Äôs no coincidence that SEVADER translated means ‚Äòto escape‚Äô. Versatile producers and equally skilled behind the decks, the duo have already graced a number of impressive stages including festivals Your Paradise and Arcadia, with many more in their sights.

Their signature production style was recognised early on by independent labels Beats of No Nation and Hot Sunday Records with support from Will Clarke, Colour Castle and more. After an extended writing trip in the US, Doorlys imprint ‚ÄòReptile Dysfunction‚Äô released the Latin-inspired 'Visions' on his Miami Music Week sampler followed closely by the Cloudbreak War Drums EP on LA collective Percomaniacs label.

After putting their spin on official remixes for Cassian, Poolclvb & Thandi Phoenix in 2019  SEVADER began curating a seasonal mix series entitled ‚ÄòSelect‚Äô which champions their favourite tracks and rewards loyal fans & followers with new material before it is officially released.

SEVADER are expected to take things to the next level in 2020 with a highly anticipated release on Club Sweat, Persian Rose is a nod to jazz, soul and the foundations of dance music. Evoking an endless Summer vibe reminiscent of their hometown Noosa, their latest efforts in the studio are poised to charm the global scene.

Pirdo is an Argentine DJ & producer, in the genres Deep House, Tech House and Minimal House.

During his teens he began to listen to local radio channels of House music. A few years later he began to experiment with different sounds, mixing House and Techno combining with various types of percussion and rhythms.

He began to venture into new sounds and achived his current sound after visiting the main influential cities in the world of the electronic music scene (such as Amsterdam, London, Ibiza, Berlin, New York, among others) and its main festivals and conferences (such as ADE, WMC, Sonus , Ultra, Loveland, Circoloco). This is reflected in the versatility of his sets, loaded with energy and groove.

He made his way to the great clubs and parties of the electronic scene in Buenos Aires, such as Moscu, La Playa Festival, Bahrein, Crobar, Brandy, Niceto Club, Rose in Rio, Esvedra, among others, and recently managed to bring his sound to Europe and the United States.

Austin, Texas-based Boogietraxx hails from New York, USA

Releases on: True Romance | InStereo Recordings | theBasement Discos | NDYD Records | Spa in Disco | Super Spicy Records | Spincat Records | Blockhead Recordings | Slightly Transformed | Shame Records

As a rhythmic renovator of retro funk, Boogietraxx offers a lens into the discoverse that brought dance music to the masses but offers a uniquely soulful and modern twist. 

Born in Staten Island, NY and now living in Austin, TX for the last few years, Boogietraxx, is helmed by producer/DJ Brandon Keeks who‚Äôs also ¬Ω of Hot Fun. And he brings an array of influences in his soundscapes that feature filter house, French touch, and filter funk. 

Brought up on a nutritious diet of Prince, Kashif, George Benson, Daft Punk, DJ Falcon, Romanthony, and countless others, Boogietraxx‚Äôs sound is rooted in the future with accentuated basslines and laser-guided melodies. 

Since moving to Austin, Brandon has teamed up with local wellness and entertainment collective, Conscious Raving, to curate dance parties with purpose, and inject a whole lot of suave disco boogie rhythm to each experience. He‚Äôs honed his skills all over the circuit at venues like Empire Control Room, Vulcan Gas Company, The Drafting Room, Indra‚Äôs Awarehouse, Voodoo Room, and more.

To date, Boogietraxx has released on Super Spicy Records, Hot Digits Music, Shame Records and more. Not only do his tracks offer something fresh out of the funk box, but his sets offer a joyful journey, oscillating anywhere from soulful vocal-driven sonatas to jackin‚Äô house stompers. There really is no limit for what discosphere Boogietraxx will ascend to, so be sure to reserve some life to get lost in the bonafide beats of Boogietraxx!

BLACK LIGHT DISCO is all about the disco, house and funk scene. The idea of Black Light Disco became a real thing when a few like-minded DJs and producers came together to put on a night showcasing the very best in disco, house and funk and everything in between. Our ethos is based around a very simple concept: GOOD MUSIC, GOOD TIMES with GOOD PEOPLE. We announced ourselves on a gorgeous sunny Saturday in June 2019 with an all day and night party in Liverpool‚Äôs thriving Baltic Triangle area. It was the start of something very special. 

We have a solid core group of musical talent hailing from England, Scotland and Wales providing perfectly cooked grooves and juicy disco basslines. The BLD team presently comprises of Esteban, Goz (Spin City) and Pookie Knights ‚Äì clocking up decades of DJ‚Äôing and dancefloor experience between them. As individuals, the BLD team have been producing consistently high quality sets over the last few years. Now, as a collective, the aim is to make Black Light Disco THE place to promote new music and to bring you the very best in established/up-and-coming artists and producers in the edits, re-edits, disco, funk and nu-disco genre. 

In January 2020, we launched a weekly show on THE biggest house music FM radio station in New York, MyHouseRadio.fm (also available digitally at www.myhouseradio.fm).  The Black Light Disco Show airs every Monday exclusive to MyHouse Radio between 7pm ‚Äì 9pm GMT (2pm -4pm EST), bringing you the finest in disco, funk and boogie; all delivered by our expert in-house Sonic Consultants (resident DJs) with guest mixes from the hottest producers, DJs and artists out there right now. 
 
No-one is safe until everyone is safe, and once we're back to whatever the 'new normal' may be we aim to carry on with the Black Light Disco live events ‚Äì possibly in a city or town near you. Want to be kept in the loop? Check us out on Facebook https://www.facebook.com/theblacklightdisco/ for future events. 

Interested in hosting a BLD event? Email us at the.blacklightdisco1@gmail.com

A Londoner now based in Norway, over the last decade, Ben has performed at music events in 35 countries including Coachella Festival in California.

Musically, Ben grew up on a diet of Motown, soul, and disco from his Mum and classical music via his Dad, while in his teenage years he discovered the raw power of hip hop and drum N bass. His 20s were then a riot of disco, house, and techno. All of these flavours coalesce into his current output and the eclectic sounds that emerge from his record label @PuzzleProjectsMusic.

Ben is also the man behind the sprawling PuzzleProjectsGroup, which operates several progressive concepts dedicated to music, artists & vibes including the chart-topping record label @PuzzleProjectsMusic, nomadic party concept @PUZZLEDParties, new record label @HOT-GROOVERS, and 360 business agency PuzzleProjectsCreate.

Renowned for working crowds with potent selections of all shades of Beatdown, Disco, House, Minimal music, Ben adds layers to his dynamic sets through his unique sample library of acapellas, sample and film clips recorded by himself and collaborating musicians.

2019 proved to be a huge year for Ben as bookings for him as a solo act and PUZZLED shows took him on a 19-country world tour in nine months, playing sell-out shows across Europe, Asia & Australia.

2021 saw Ben kick off with the release of 'The Ego Death EP' on @PuzzleProjectsMusic - created with German Musician and Live act @RonaldChristoph - the EP has been receiving great acclaim including breaking into the @Beatport top 100 Tech House Charts.

The rest of 2021 & into 2022 sees Ben release multiple EPs under his name and pseudonym ‚Äò@ProfessorPuzzleOfficial‚Äô on digital & vinyl on @PuzzleProjectsMusic. record label and go on tours of North & South America, Asia & Europe.

Hailing from Scotland, Goz has been DJ‚Äôing for over 25 years and in that time has embraced a number of genres from house, hip hop and soul to disco and funk. In the early 1990s he was introduced to the art of mixing vinyl records and from that point forwards, Goz immersed himself in the art of beat matching and building sets - crafting his unique style throughout the 1990s where he would play local parties and get-togethers and, of course  - the all-important pre and post-night out shenanigans.  

After taking a break from DJ‚Äôing in the early 2000s, Goz picked up the reins once again in 2014 and got back to doing what he loves most. Goz has always had an exceptionally diverse taste in music, although he naturally gravitated towards disco, soul, funk and hip-hop genres. 

Goz‚Äôs passion for music shines through in his sets, which are carefully curated and crafted to take you on a journey that always leaves you craving more. As one of the most renowned specialists in slow-mo and laid back grooves, when Goz decides to drop down the gears he creates a ‚Äòsoundscape‚Äô experience few DJs on the scene can achieve. Similarly, when the disco juices are flowing, and the BPM is cranked up it‚Äôs a roller coaster ride and swirling haze of funky basslines, heavenly string arrangements, Afro beats and soulful smokiness. 

As host / show runner of the hugely successful Spin City which airs on New York‚Äôs number one House Music Station, www.myhouseradio.fm for a number of years now, Goz has built an extensive and strong follower base who regularly tune in to the two hour show which airs every Sunday at 7pm GMT (2pm NYC). The format of Spin City is a certified winner - with Goz normally presenting the first hour of the show followed by a special guest mix each week. On occasion, Goz will take the whole two hours to treat listeners to prime selections of new, old and classic tracks.  Some of the biggest names on the disco and nu-disco scene have appeared on the show, which has also secured talents such as John Le Visiteur, IMFROMULL, DJ Wahine and Queen & Disco for bi-monthly and quarterly residency spots. Goz also has a keen eye for up-and-coming DJs and producers - spotting undiscovered talent early and giving them a platform to showcase their skills.

During the summer of 2019, Goz teamed up with a group of like-minded DJs and producers to form a new promotion - Black Light Disco. The first Black Light Disco event in June 2019 was an enormous success and has gone on to land its own radio show which also airs on MyHouse Radio FM every Monday from 7pm - 9pm GMT (2pm - 4pm NYC). Since the show started in January 2020, its reputation has grown considerably and BLD now attracts some of the biggest names on the disco and nu-disco scene for guest spots. In May 2020, Black Light Disco formed a partnership with the excellent Samosa Records and Daje Funk Records to present a monthly residency on the MyHouse Radio platform, with label head honchos Les Inferno and De Gama taking over the show for the whole two hours. Airing on the second Monday of each month, The Samosa Funk show is already taking the disco world by storm -the partnership with BLD really taking things to the next level for the promotion. Going forward, Black Light Disco has a number of live events planned, so watch this space for the most up-to-date news on where one of Black Light Disco‚Äôs now famous nights will drop next!

If you listen to the shows please do leave a comment (positive or negative!) and check out the amazingly talented DJs, producers and artists who feature.

Greg began collecting vinyl and DJing in the early 90s, spinning various forms of house music at events in Birmingham, Coventry and then London, eventually playing at famous venues such as SW1 and The Cross.

Throughout the 00s, he regularly went to, and occasionally played at, Brixton-based club night Gettin‚Äô Hectic, where the music policy was far more eclectic and varied, but still absolutely rocking. Inspired by these influential club nights, and the emerging Edits scene in the latter part of that decade, Greg set about developing his own eclectic style - all underpinned by two key ingredients - groove and soul.

Greg has since held a three-year residency at one of London‚Äôs long-established venues, the Big Chill Bar, gaining a reputation for his epic, genre-hopping sets spanning Funk, Soul, Hip-hop, Disco, Nu-Disco, House and beyond. In 2018,  he started his own club night in South-West London - Borderline - bringing his eclectic, funky vibe to the local area and culminating in several sold out events. When COVID-19 hit in March 2020, Greg launched the virtual Borderline Lockdown Sessions, doing live streams on Saturday nights throughout the pandemic, with lively chatrooms and a growing following.

Priding himself on spinning different sets each time out, his meticulous track selection and coherent blend of different genres will be sure to keep your attention from start to finish.

Future House Music (FHM) is one of electronic music‚Äôs fastest growing independent record labels. Founded by Aart van den Dool & Gino van Eijk in 2014, the label has grown into a close-knit community around the globe, reaching 1 million YouTube subscribers within only 4 years. The idea of starting Future House Music was to create an online platform for the niche music of Future House back in 2014, where fans and artists shared their love for music. The platform organically found more traction, from there we decided to evolve into a record label in 2015. Fast forward, the independent label has over 300 releases to date and hosts showcases and festival stages across the world, whilst launching the FHM merchandise line. With a team of 5 based in hometown Rotterdam, Future House Music aims to be at the forefront of electronic dance music, connecting and evolving together with the most exciting talents and artists today. Our mission & vision statement is: creating a world-class house community to champion artists and fans, by setting trends, challenging the status quo, and sharing the passion for house music.

It was in 2011 that Dutch pair Lars Dales and Maarten Smeets quickly broke through in the electronic music scene. Since then they have become known for their widescreen approach to making and playing club-ready grooves. From deep to disco, tech to soul, they join the dots between the past and the present with their own sense of storytelling and do so in clubs around the world, as well as in their own studio. House might be the root of the Dam Swindle sound, but it takes nourishment from a much wider world of music. 

It was their early, high impact tunes such as 'The Wrap Around' and 'The Break Up', that got dancers all over the world in a frenzy. Since then, the pair has constantly evolved and matured and continued to draw on all musical niches. Building bridges between them, their  landmark 2018 album High Life or their ‚ÄòCoffee in the Morning EP' both furthered their take on house music with a real sense of timelessness and class.

Since 2013, the pair has also established their own Heist Recordings as a well respected label that is home to the majority of their own originals, though other underground mainstays such as Aus Music and Classic Music Company have also come calling. Heist is more than just a label, though - it is a breeding ground for talents old and new; somewhere talent is nurtured and allowed to develop.  Label showcases and special projects such as the yearly Roundup EP;  where all artists from the past 12 months remix each other after a random selection process, furthers the family vibe and helps Heist stand out from crowd. Artists such as Nebraska, Adryiano, Kassian, Demuir, Makez, Max Graef, P√©p√© Bradock, Nachtbraker, Matthew Herbert, Ge-Ology, Byron the Aquarius and many more have all contributed, proving that it is a place for unrestrained creatives to be free with their own sonic visions. The label looks as good as it sounds, too, thanks to visual artist Bas Koopmans's standout artwork designs. 
 
Proof of Dam Swindle's widescreen approach to production is their long and talented list of collaborators, which includes the likes of acclaimed musician, Eric Clapton and John Mayer collaborator and Blue Note artist Tom Misch, US talent Seven Davis Jr., instrumental collective Jungle by Night, plus Marc de Clive-Lowe, Jitwam and Lorenz Rhode. Next to their own originals, a broad spectrum of artists have asked Dam Swindle for some of their special remix magic: on labels like Strut and Soundway they have reworked the legendary Pat Thomas, aka the ‚ÄòGolden voice of Africa,' and gave his single ‚ÄòYamona‚Äô a contemporary electronic edge, as well as The Mauskovic Dance Band‚Äôs track ‚ÄòSpace Drum Machine‚Äô and plenty more artists like Kerri Chandler, Mayer Hawthorne and Tom Misch. As their talent for bridging genres from all over the world continues to attract global attention, high profile projects keep rolling in from all points on the musical globe. 

Dam Swindle are famously avid collectors of both old and new records, and it shows in their DJ sets, which keep you on your toes as they move freely and skillfully through different times, places and sounds. Rather than limiting themselves to a certain feeling or mood, Dam Swindle can call on classic house, obscure disco, African funk, soulful techno and plenty in between, all with the aim of making those special moments that crowds never forget. It is for that reason that their name has become a real stamp of authority and invention in the dance music world. Whatever they do, then, this pair do with irresistible charm.

Christian Drew is a composer, performer and teacher based in London. He makes music for concerts, installation, dance and film using acoustic instruments, electronics, recordings and objects. Current interests include looseness, intuition, blurring, singing, thingness, materiality, dyads and shoegazing.

Recent works have been composed for Plus Minus Ensemble, EXAUDI Vocal Ensemble, London Symphony Orchestra Players, Juice Vocal Ensemble, Kreutzer Quartet, OUT-TAKE Ensemble, What Guitar Trio, lutenist Elizabeth Kenny and soprano Juliet Fraser at the Wigmore Hall, The Place Theatre, IKLECTIK, the National Centre for Early Music, 840 Series, Cheltenham Music Festival and the Richmond Concert Society. Currently he is a participant on the LSO Panufnik Composers Scheme 2020-21.

Christian recently graduated with a Master of Composition with Distinction from the Guildhall School of Music and Drama, where he studied as a Leverhulme Arts Scholar with Laurence Crane and Richard Baker. Here he received the Mary Ryan Composition Award and the Rose Lawrence Horners‚Äô Award, the Guildhall School‚Äôs academic prize.

He completed his undergraduate degree at the University of Southampton, studying with Matthew Shlomowitz, Benjamin Oliver and Michael Finnissy. Upon graduation he received the Hazel Muras-Osborn Composition Prize, the Lyttel Prize and the Edward Wood Memorial Prize for academic achievement. He was also Assistant Conductor of the Southampton University Symphony Orchestra.

As a multi-instrumentalist Christian has performed with a range of bands and experimental projects on fretted instruments, accordion, voice, objects and electronics. He currently teaches guitar, ukulele, banjo and music theory privately and in schools across the South East. In addition to his work as a teacher, Christian is in frequent demand as an orchestrator, copyist and engraver, working with orchestras, publishers and composers of concert and film music.

Christian‚Äôs work and studies have been supported by the H R Taylor Charitable Trust, Archbishop Abbot‚Äôs Exhibition Foundation, Split Infinitive Trust, Leverhulme Trust, Guildhall School Trust and Help Musicians UK.

Sound has the power to heal.   As a musician I had always thought of music as art, and a way to entertain, but I have now started to look at music and sound in a new light. 

During an experience with extreme anxiety, I found music to be a valuable tool for helping me to work through it. Later, in order to understand more about what was going on with me (and to prove to myself that I wasn't completely insane), I started to read more about psychology and neuroscience and spirituality and anything that related to the "inner world" that I had re-discovered. Through this experience, I discovered the powerful value of music (frequency, sound and rhythm).  I was always attracted to the mysterious nature of music and sound, but now I see it's potential as a healing force and something that can be helpful for other people. In the process have also learned a lot about different mental states (states of consciousness) and how sound and frequency can help me to access and focus my mind in these states. 

Music is the study and artful use of frequencies, but in essence our whole world is frequency. Science acknowledges that everything is vibrating, from solid matter and our brainwaves down to the activity of the smallest particles we know of. The world we live in is a world of vibration. A world of music!

So, this is what has inspired me to start this SoundCloud page.  I have been working on music and sounds (mainly recording nature sounds, so far) not only for my own self therapy, but also to share with family and friends that had told me that they were dealing with similar issues (or just wanted music for meditation or for relaxing.) This is still an exploration for me and I hope you'll find this helpful in your life.

Christian Vasseur had been learning the guitar on his own for some time when he met his first teacher Pascal Bo√´ls. 
Then, he took classes at the Conservatoire de Lille with Jean-Philippe Gr√ºneissen and discovered the Renaissance Lute with Eug√®ne Ferr√© at the Conservatoire de Toulouse for four years and took classes with renown Lute players such as Paul O'Dette and Yasunori Imamura. Practicing the Lute made him curious of improvisation and oriental music. At this time he began to perform on stage with various bands or solo, playing Early music with the Lute as well as contemporary music with the guitar. 
After several years of Early music repertory, He chose to dedicate himself to stage performance and music writing. At this stage, he started introducing some acting in his performances, mixing acoustic and electronic sounds, improvised and written pieces. 
For 15 years, he has been teaching musical theater and free improvisation classes to various groups of people : 
children and adults teen-agers in custody at the Maison d'Arr√™t de Loos ; 
disabled adults and children (Compagnie de l'Oiseau Mouche at Roubaix, Ecole de Pratique Th√©√¢trale at Villeneuve d'Ascq, psychatric hospital of Saint-Andr√© ). Meeting with highly vulnerable or helpless people has had a deep influence on the way he works today. 
Christian Vasseur has composed many pieces of music for various instruments and bands. Truly motivated by the possibilities offered by music applied to other disciplines, he works with video artists, dance and theatrical companies.

The Christian Vasseur' music borrows as much from classical tradition as from popular music. It is free of any form of dogma. As a polymorphic musician he every often takes part into interdisciplinary events where music combines itself with other artistic media, such as photography, video, dance and theatre. In theatrical events, his music acts as a counterpoint to the text, creating an extra voice, sometimes melodic, sometimes dissonant or noisy, based on the requirements of the staging, where acoustic and electronic sounds usually intermingle. Christian Vasseur plays lute too and composes new original music for this instrument. On top of solo concerts,he usually plays in a duet with cello player Jean-Christophe Lannoy (N‚ÄôGaddi), with guitar player Philippe Lenglet (Soliloques en loque, free improvisation), with belgian guitar player Gilbert Isbin (Bubble Fauna, free improvisation), with electronic music composer Denis Streibig (Les Chromonautes) with Djuwel (trio with singer and lute player Habib Guerroumi and Jean-Christophe Lannoy, two albums on Playa Sound label). He founded the band Mr Agata which plays tinny electro hardbarock opera music (La vie d'un homme on Dog Eared records). With the comedian musician Patrick Sourdeval he founded the duet Chamane/Shamane. He joined the electric guitars quartet OGR in 2010 and create the duet Fire Walk With Us with the eight string guitar player Steve Gibbs in 2018. Two CDs (Alam and Po√®mes saturniens) was edited in may 2009 by Humming Conch.

He is not interested in the use of the flutes as ‚Äúacademic instruments‚Äù, he has given up on traditional techniques in favour of extended techniques like un-pitched breaths, multiple sounds, harmonics, overtones, whispers, microtones, keys percussion, and other sounds, all combined with breath, silence, soundscapes‚Ä¶ exploring the acoustic possibility of the flutes, in the sound space and in relation with other improvisers.

About Gianni Teleska

Boards of Britain is the STAGE name I use for fronting my music. So who is Boards of Britain then? The man behind the music of Boards of Britain is Gianni Teleska (also known as Gianni Van Heusen) ,hailing from the Eternal City Rome / London UK & Sound Engineer Giacomo Fazio aka DJ Bokuwa .
My musical past is now very varied and I have over the last 25 years had a lot of tracks over various music HOSTING sites, but I have kind of settled here on the cloud, to date i have roughly 15000 Vinyls & Cds in total which I am chuffed with as it means my music is getting out there and obviously listened to, which is my goal.
I like a lot of styles such as Trance Hardhouse Freeform Acid Techno Ambient Psycadelic & Techno but usually prefer the electronic / synth genre and listen to anything from Kraftwerk / Tangerine Dream / Andy Pickford / Synthetik / Gary Numan / Vangelis / JMJ / I also like classic C64 SID chip tunes from the MASTERS like Rob Hubbard and Martin Galway, the missing master Pete Namlook & Klause Schulze etc, right up to modern cult artists like Armin Van Buuren, Daniel Kandi, Super8 & tab, Above & Beyond, Rank 1,Ferry Corsten, the Man Himself Paul Oakenfold without wich today we couldn‚Äôt have Music but the list is endless!!!....all these bands have influenced my musical style and approach greatly.
Our Set & Pa Lives and so my music always describe a story or depict feelings therefore our set are not only pieces of banging electronic dance music, but also representations of plenty of emotions, our base was the Eternal City Rome Approaching Music back on time were Acid House was in charge , then the world was devastated by the Techno Sound from Detroit so we were part of the Italian Techno Scene with Centro Suono Rave on Radio Centro Suono in Rome and by The 3Immaginary Boys & Marco Carola on the Parteneopean Music Scene of Naples, after around 1994 the Trance & Progressive Sound took over the World.

We moved back to London in 1996 surfing the Underground sound of Tony De Vit , Steve Thomas & Pete Wardman and witnessing the born of the Hardhouse Music, we were part of the majors Hardhouse & Psycadelic Music Events & Raves such as Escape From Samsara, Return to The Source, Trancentral, Pendragon and all the Events at The Fridge Club & Bar, George IV & Brixton Accademy in London along side our Friends & Dj Legends Zebedee, Gizelle, Mark Sinclair, Captain Tinrib and the one & only Tony De Vit at Trade
Boards of Britain 's vision combines the DRIVING forces of trance / electronic / synth music and shakes them into the ultimate electro cocktail with hard, fast and kicking basslines and drums with soaring lead lines and melodies.. all of these elements when combined make the tracks of our Set & Live Pa Radio Show memorable and foot tapping at the same time!

2014 was a memorable year for me because also I had the pleasure of meeting & work with Andrea Doria the most Influential Dj & Electronic Producer out of Italy, Bucci Bug was his best selling out Record, almost 3.5 milion copy selled around the World , along side Him we were making MINDFORM EP, a music Project of 4 set of Experimental Trance & Electronic Ambient Music to celebrate Federico Keegan an astonishing Electronic & Techno Producer out of Brazil.

Released in early 2016, the Astral Ambient EP was dedicated to the loving Memory of Sound Engineer Giacomo Fazio aka Dj Bokuwa who saddenly died on our last performance at the Fridge Club in Brixton London, now Boards of Britain raised from dust thanks to Sound Engineer Alessio Circi Aka Ix Prospectum of Dast recordings who come out from Berlin and reform along side Gianni Teleska the new Conception of their Music. Their sound continue to develop; growing in intensity and twisting into more complex, aggressive, and euphorically bent shapes

I'm Stan Magendanz & I love listening to & creating Ambient, Dark Ambient & Experimental electronica (and the occasional beatscape). I have no professional aspirations  - I just really like creating music / manipulating sounds. It's my way of relaxing after a hard day at the office. All my tracks are produced using monitoring headphones (Sennheiser HD 280 Pro) so I recommend that you listen to my music through headphones. My DAWs of choice are FL Studio & Studio One. I also use Reason 11 every now & then. 

All tracks are downloadable and covered by a Creative Commons license. Collaborations / Remixes are welcome so feel free to experiment - no need to get my permission first. Just send me a link to your track when you're done :)

To the artists I follow; I do my best to try to listen to as many of your tracks as possible each night (I listen to each track all the way through - you went through the effort to create a track so you deserve to have it heard in full). If I miss a recent upload of yours, please forgive me...

Thank you for taking the time to visit my little corner of the soundcloud. 
P.S. I am also an enthusiastic cryptocurrency investor. XRP, XDC, XLM & HBAR will make you rich one day - look into them :)

Mogano is the moniker of the electronic music producer Marco Berardi.
Based in Berlin since 2012, his sonic work is developed around re-processing traditional musical instruments into soundscapes and doomy, polyrhythmical drums textures. 
Exploring techno, ambient, experimental and bass music spectrum both as Dj and Live performer, his music has been hosted at Contort (NewCodes - Berlin Atonal), Flussi Media Art Festival (IT), Tresor Berlin, ATOM Festival (Ukraine), OHM Berlin, Saturnalia Macao (IT), Krake Festival (Berlin), Freqs Of Nature (DE), Spektrum - Art Science Community (DE),  RoBOt Festival(IT) amongst many others. 
  
Since 2013 he is also curator and co-owner of Arboretum, an imprint founded with the visual designer Andrea Familari/FAX.

Above & Beyond and long-time collaborator Justine Suissa share their first joint effort in over four years, ‚ÄòAlmost Home‚Äô. 

‚ÄòAlmost Home‚Äô is Above & Beyond‚Äôs first club track of 2021, arriving just in time for their Group Therapy 450 milestone show at The Drumsheds in London this September. ABGT450 is their first headline show in over a year, and will see the trio perform to an audience of more than 10,000 fans. Later in September, Above & Beyond embark on the Anjunafamily Reunion Tour, which visits major cities across the U.S.A. including sold-out stops at Red Rocks Amphitheatre, Stanford‚Äôs Frost Amphitheater and the world-famous Echostage in D.C. 

Jono, Tony, Paavo and Justine have been working together since 2000 when they formed the group OceanLab. In 2008, they released their first and only album ‚ÄòSirens Of The Sea‚Äô,a record that has gained near-mythical status among trance fans. More recently, Above & Beyond and Justine have collaborated on club hits like ‚ÄòAlright Now‚Äô, ‚ÄòCold Feet‚Äô and ‚ÄòAnother Chance‚Äô, and emotive, downtempo records like ‚ÄòLittle Something‚Äô. 

In 2016, Justine joined Above & Beyond during their sell-out ‚ÄòAcoustic II‚Äô tour, which stopped at iconic venues including Royal Albert Hall in London and The Hollywood Bowl in Los Angeles. 

‚ÄúThis is a track that we originally wrote with Justine some years ago. Like many musicians during lockdown, we buried ourselves in the studio and had plenty of time to pick through old ideas. ‚ÄòAlmost Home‚Äô, with its ‚Äô80s production influences, caught our ear. We sent it across to Justine again, and she rewrote the second verse to reflect her feelings on it today - we won‚Äôt tell you what it‚Äôs about though, we‚Äôll leave that for you to decide. This track started in quite a different form, so we‚Äôve also done a Club Mix to bring it a bit more up-to-date. It‚Äôs quite emotional to think that we‚Äôll be able to play this one live for you all very soon. Take care for now!‚Äù - Above & Beyond

‚ÄòAlmost Home‚Äô is out August 20th on Anjunabeats. Tickets for Above & Beyond‚Äôs Anjunafamily Reunion tour are available now.

All the way from Melbourne, Australia Bangerz & Masherz (Boz & Rob G) formed a music partnership duo in 2009 and together they have forged a fresh, driving, hard trance vibe to their tracks with dark techy stabs, mega phat bass drops and dark melodic breaks.They have supported names like Scot Project, Uberdruck, Proteus, Wildstylez, Yoji, Alex Kidd, Technoboy and more....

All of their tracks have made it into the top 20 on 'trackitdown and beatport' and are always supported by the big names in the hard dance scene. Some of their biggest tracks have been Digital Wasteland, Virus in me and their remix of Hardforze & Halu Suzuki - Drop it which have all gone straight to No.1. 

Bangerz & Masherz have been proud supporters of the Gearbox brand and have always be pushing fresh unique hard dance sounds.

The main thing with Bangerz & Masherz apart from their music is that they always enjoy the creative process of producing unique sounds and pushing musical boundaries for tearing up future audiences.

In 2016 B&M have decided to hang up the headphones for production and performing. 

Some final words....

''We will miss those rough relentless bass lines and rocking crowds that have made us proud.... but the time has come to move on.. We will no longer be making hard dance tracks but we will continue to produce music''

Thankyou for the memories...

It‚Äôs been amazing twenty years since me and my friends started organizing illegal raves in the squat houses of Helsinki in early 90s. Most bizarre experience must have been DJing for Jean-Paul Gaultier and Helena Christensen at a Berlin fetish club Kit Kat after their first ever Berlin show. Most flashy ones have been entertaining the rich & famous of Hong Kong or Russia while warming up Chemical Brothers, Paul van Dyk or Underworld was something I‚Äôll never forget. From the venues I‚Äôve DJed Tresor in Berlin, Pacha in Ibiza, Ministry of Sound in London and CODE in Tokyo were special places to play.

My recording career started in 1998 with Slusnik Luna‚Äôs Nicklas Renqvist. ‚ÄòUnity‚Äò was signed to british Steelfish label and found it‚Äôs way to Gatecrasher and Renaissance compilations. Sasha and Oakenfold opened their Essential Mixes with it and Pete Tong played it on BBC Radio 1. Gigs with DJ Tiesto lead into signing to his Black Hole label while other releases include ‚ÄòEmbrace‚Äô on Five AM and ‚ÄòBeautiful‚Äò on Sential (finnish national singles chart #1). Most famous colaborations include ‚ÄòYearZero‚Äò together with Andy Moor, ‚ÄòGod‚Äôs Garden‚Äò together with David West and ‚ÄòZeitgeist‚Äò with Solarstone. My remixes include Aalto‚Äôs ‚ÄòRush‚Äò made together with Super8, Stage One remix made for Hooj Choons, Way Out West‚Äôs ‚ÄòKilla‚Äò and more recently a bootleg remix of Hans Zimmer‚Äôs ‚ÄòTime‚Äò from Inception soundtrack which Paul Oakenfold loved so much he did his own edit. In 2011 I released my third artist album ‚Äú20‚Äù which also celebrates my twenty years of DJing.

As promoters we have come a very long way from the days of illegal warehouse raves. Together with my friends, we have run Club Unity for over ten years, promoted Renaissance‚Äôs events in Helsinki and organized events called ‚ÄúPacifique‚Äù for almost 3000 people in a water park. We have had fun at 16 hour Sunday clubbing sessions at DTM and have brought Jose Padilla to Finland. We have organised events on boats, in parks, on ice-skating rinks and even did one of Finland‚Äôs first flash mobs: the infamous One Minute Raves. The longest set I‚Äôve ever played was 23 hours on New Year‚Äôs Day in 2010. To me electronic music and club culture has always been about open-mindness, unity amongst people and pushing the musical boundaries forward, whether it‚Äôs ambient concert in a park or full on rave in warehouse. Uniting the sounds, the minds, the people‚Ä¶

With a growing stack of heralded EPs and a long list of aliases, dabbling in all facets of electronic dance, Tech Support stands amongst some of the most prolific DJs and producers out there. Yet despite a vigorous work ethic the young artist still maintains a sense of playfulness and irreverence in his work, demonstrated by his tongue-in-cheek curation of communist memes and quippy referential track names (‚ÄòThat Record With Friends On It‚Äô ring any bells?).

Combining lashings of house euphoria, mind-melting chug, dirty basement disco, obscure italo and more, Tech Support is primed and ready to send you offworld to a strange yet familiar place of feel good, immersive dance music. And it‚Äôs not just dancefloor clientele that have been captured by these far-out frequencies, gaining support from the likes of Mixmag, Rinse FM, Houseum and fellow artists Black Loops, Late Nite Tuff Guy, and Dan Shake on a number of productions and mixes.


Releasing both digitally and on 12‚Äù wax you can find his work immortalised on a number of labels including Nocturne, Silver Bear Recordings, Together Alone Records, plus dive deeper still into his wealth of self-released edits and re-imaginings of iconic club tracks, each more infectious than the last. Alongside his talents as a producer Tech Support has moulded himself into an impressive crate digger and DJ too, cutting his teeth through deep, explorative sets and regular radio residencies at spaces like Mick‚Äôs Garage and stations like 1BTN, Threads, Netil, SWU FM and current monthly home Balamii respectively.  

Out on the festival circuit Tech Support has played stages on both home soil and overseas via Alfresco Festival in Tunbridge Wells to Defected in Croatia, and Tenby‚Äôs Westival to Solas in Dublin. Known for his effortless and intricate sets, Tech Support‚Äôs record bag is forever deep and his creative mind always ticking; equally comfortable locked in a disco groove or deftly joining the dots between sonic obscurities like darkwave and italo, he‚Äôs an artist capable of fully expressing himself unbounded by the limits of conventional genre narratives.

Cosmico, contemporaneo.\n\nSound engineer, selector and music producer based in Milan, Italy. He is currently a leading figure in the alternative cultural Italian scene. His meticulous musical research reflects an eclectic style characterized by an Italian attitude which is the expression of the love for his land and its traditions. Tracing a music-temporal path that comes from folk sounds mixed with contemporary electronic and experimental techniques. He takes inspiration from the environment that surrounds him and breaks down the boundaries between the genres, blending its musical influences and reinterpreting its origins with a propensity towards the future. He offers refined, evocative and always different emotional performances, tailor-made to the audience without ever abandoning his own music identity.

‚ÄúFribourg, Switzerland. Back in the old days, in the historical center, everyone used to heat with wood. According to urban legend, the Rababou (from the Fribourg patois ‚Äúrababou√™t‚Äù) was a wood thief. But there was very little firewood in the area. The legend tells that the Rababou went to steal wood from the forests of the Gott√©ron Valley, which belonged to the rich of the high society. \n\nRababoo is inspired by the creature that represents all vices and bad habits of the town. Every year at Carnival, we put him on trial and burn him at stake to celebrate the end of winter and request a rich summer (as long as seasons still exist). Rababoo is about the tradition to celebrate, it is a ritual to reflect the good and the bad. Rababoo is about an acceptance of all kinds of musical backgrounds driven by the same passion for music sharing. Rababoo accelerates the collapse for a better rebuilding.\"
